.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-device - Enroll and maintain this machine as a personal device on your org's network


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel device [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Device mode connects a personal machine (laptop, workstation) to your
organization's AceTeam Network with a durable, self-healing identity.

.PP
Unlike 'citadel init' (which provisions a compute node), device mode runs no
workloads. It enrolls this machine once via a browser approval, then keeps its
network membership alive automatically: when the session breaks or its key
nears expiry, the device proves its identity with a certificate and rejoins
without any human involvement.

.PP
Requires the Tailscale client to be installed (device mode drives it; it does
not replace it).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for device


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-device-enroll(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-device-install(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-device-run(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-device-status(1)\fP, \fBcitadel-device-uninstall(1)\fP
